"title": "1040: God, fatherhood of",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "1040",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Primarily signifying God's paternal relationship to Jesus Christ, the term also refers to God's fatherly relationship to his creation, especially to believers as the “children of God”.</p>\n<h2>Aspects of the fatherhood of God</h2>\n<h3>He is the Creator and provider</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor8:6\">1CO 8:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut32:6\">DEU 32:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut32:18\">DEU 32:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa64:8\">ISA 64:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts17:24-Acts17:28\">ACT 17:24–17:28</a></p>\n<h3>He shows love and compassion</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos11:1\">HOS 11:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps103:13\">PSA 103:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer3:19\">JER 3:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor1:3\">2CO 1:3</a></p>\n<h3>He exercises his providence and care</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps68:5\">PSA 68:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt6:26\">MAT 6:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt6:31-Matt6:33\">MAT 6:31–6:33</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke12:29-Luke12:31\">LUK 12:29–12:31</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt7:11\">MAT 7:11</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke11:13\">LUK 11:13</a></p>\n<h3>He disciplines and corrects</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut8:5\">DEU 8:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov3:11-Prov3:12\">PRO 3:11–3:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb12:5-Heb12:6\">HEB 12:5–12:6</a></p>\n<h2>God as the Father of Jesus Christ</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt3:17\">MAT 3:17</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark1:11\">MRK 1:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke3:22\">LUK 3:22</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt11:27\">MAT 11:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke2:49\">LUK 2:49</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John5:17-John5:18\">JHN 5:17–5:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John17:11\">JHN 17:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John20:17\">JHN 20:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom15:6\">ROM 15:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph1:3\">EPH 1:3</a><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet1:3\">1PE 1:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John1:3\">1JN 1:3</a></p>\n<h2>God is the father of Israel</h2>\n<h3>He cares for his covenant people</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer31:9\">JER 31:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod4:22\">EXO 4:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut14:1\">DEU 14:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut32:6\">DEU 32:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut32:18\">DEU 32:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa63:16\">ISA 63:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mal2:10\">MAL 2:10</a></p>\n<h3>He is the father of the kings of Israel</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam7:13-2Sam7:14\">2SA 7:13–7:14</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr17:12-1Chr17:13\">1CH 17:12–17:13</a> <em>This description of God's fatherhood involves the maintenance of a special relationship between God and David's descendants, which ultimately includes Jesus Christ.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps2:7\">PSA 2:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps89:26-Ps89:27\">PSA 89:26–89:27</a></p>\n<h2>God is the father of Christian believers</h2>\n<h3>He has an intimate relationship with believers</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt6:9\">MAT 6:9</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke11:2\">LUK 11:2</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John20:17\">JHN 20:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor6:18\">2CO 6:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal3:26\">GAL 3:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John2:13\">1JN 2:13</a></p>\n<h3>He adopts believers into his family</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John1:12-John1:13\">JHN 1:12–1:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:14-Rom8:17\">ROM 8:14–8:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal4:5-Gal4:7\">GAL 4:5–4:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John3:1\">1JN 3:1</a></p>\n<h2>The fatherhood of God has implications for the church</h2>\n<h3>Character: children are to reproduce the Father's likeness</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:48\">MAT 5:48</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Unity: one Father means one family</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:3-Eph4:6\">EPH 4:3–4:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mal2:10\">MAL 2:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt23:9\">MAT 23:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph3:14-Eph3:15\">EPH 3:14–3:15</a></p>\n<h3>Status: believers are related to Jesus Christ</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt12:50\">MAT 12:50</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark3:35\">MRK 3:35</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke8:21\">LUK 8:21</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:29\">ROM 8:29</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb2:11\">HEB 2:11</a></p>\n<h3>Inheritance: believers are heirs of the Father's kingdom</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:17\">ROM 8:17</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke12:32\">LUK 12:32</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal3:29\">GAL 3:29</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col1:12\">COL 1:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus3:7\">TIT 3:7</a></p>\n<h3>Submission: believers are to revere the Father</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet1:17\">1PE 1:17</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt6:9\">MAT 6:9</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke11:2\">LUK 11:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph3:14\">EPH 3:14</a></p>",
